{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S2 — Deploy Gerrit + review-bot receiver (docker-compose) behind nginx + TLS\n\n## Why\nRun Gerrit and the **review-bot webhook receiver** as the two containers on the box, reachable\nover HTTPS at `rebar.solutions.navateam.com`. Gerrit needs a `%2F`-safe reverse proxy — the\ncommunity uses nginx/Apache, NOT Caddy (Caddy URL-decodes paths by default with no global\nswitch, which breaks Gerrit's change/project screens; no confirmed Caddy+Gerrit recipe exists).\nThis is the bottom layer of the d251 \"proven pipe\": Gerrit serving, the receiver reachable over\nHTTP, TLS terminated, secrets from SSM. NOTE (peer-pattern correction): Gerrit POSTs webhook\nJSON, not MCP protocol — so the right component is a thin HTTP **webhook receiver that IMPORTS\nthe review kernel as a library**, NOT the stdio rebar-MCP server exposed over HTTP (a FastMCP\nHTTP transport would reject a Gerrit webhook by spec; `streamable-http` is a red herring here).\n\n## What\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`:\n  - official `gerritcodereview/gerrit` pinned to a PATCH tag (e.g. `3.14.1`) with persistent\n    volumes (git/index/cache/etc/db on the data volume) + the two-step init. DERISK NOTE (E4):\n    bare minor tags `3.14`/`3.13` do NOT exist on Docker Hub; pin a published patch tag\n    (`3.14.1`/`3.13.7`/`3.12.8`), all of which publish arm64 manifests.\n  - the **review-bot container** (signing key + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY sourced from SSM into the boot\n    `.env` — see secrets bullet; write-gating as needed); both `restart: unless-stopped`, pinned\n    tags. The receiver calls the `rebar.llm` library functions DIRECTLY, so the LLM review path is\n    enabled simply by `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` being present + the `[agents]` extra being installed —\n    there is NO separate allow-flag for direct library calls (`REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` gates only the\n    stdio MCP server's tool wrappers, which this receiver does not use, so it is intentionally not\n    set).\n  - the Gerrit data volume is declared **`external: true`** (created once, outside compose) so a\n    stray `docker compose down -v` cannot destroy git/NoteDb/index state. S2 only DECLARES this\n    external data volume; volume snapshotting + retention is owned by **S7's DLM daily-snapshot\n    policy** (see S7), and the restore procedure is in the runbook. Freeze-and-restore (the d251\n    recovery posture, no break-glass v1) operates against the snapshots S7 manages.\n- **Review-bot webhook receiver (in-scope S2 deliverable).** The second container is a thin\n  **webhook->review->vote receiver** (an ASGI/FastAPI service under `src/rebar/review_bot/`)\n  that IMPORTS the review kernel as a library and exposes a plain HTTP endpoint Gerrit's\n  `webhooks` plugin POSTs to. This is deliberately NOT the stdio rebar-MCP server over HTTP\n  (Gerrit speaks webhooks, not MCP JSON-RPC; an MCP HTTP transport would reject the request).\n  The stdio MCP server is unchanged and remains for agent use only. The receiver binds\n  `0.0.0.0:<PORT>` (default `8000`); nginx routes\n  `location /review/ { proxy_pass http://review-bot:<PORT>/; }`. Decision recorded in\n  `docs/adr/0007-review-bot-receiver.md`.\n- `gerrit.config`: `container.heapLimit=2g` with `core.packedGitLimit` budgeted INSIDE the heap\n  (~512m-1g), NoteDb, `canonicalWebUrl=https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/`, sshd/httpd thread\n  caps + `sshd.batchThreads` to avoid parallel-clone OOM.\n- nginx + certbot (Let's Encrypt) terminating TLS on 443: route Gerrit (`%2F`-safe: `proxy_pass`\n  with no path) and the receiver (`location /review/`) behind the one cert; Gerrit SSH on 29418.\n- **certbot renewal lifecycle.** Initial issuance AND renewal: a systemd timer (or cron) runs\n  `certbot renew` twice daily with a deploy-hook that reloads nginx; nginx serves an\n  `/.well-known/acme-challenge/` location (webroot) so HTTP-01 renewal succeeds. Installed by\n  the bootstrap script.\n- **secrets bootstrap (SSM -> ephemeral `.env`).** `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` runs\n  `aws ssm get-parameter --with-decryption` for the signing key + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (via the\n  **instance role**, no static keys) and writes a root-only (`0600`) `.env` that compose reads,\n  BEFORE `docker compose up`. The `.env` is gitignored + ephemeral (regenerated each boot, never\n  committed); the script is idempotent and **aborts** if SSM is unreachable (never reuses a\n  stale `.env`). Recorded in `docs/adr/0008-secrets-source-ssm.md`.\n- **IAM instance role (least privilege).** Grants `ssm:GetParameter`/`GetParameters` scoped to\n  the project parameter-path prefix only (e.g.\n  `arn:aws:ssm:us-east-1:896586841071:parameter/rebar/prod/*`) plus `kms:Decrypt` on the\n  SecureString key — no wildcard. Defined in the infra IaC.\n- **observability (minimal).** Both containers log via `journald`; a health probe hits `/` and\n  the receiver `/review/` health path; a disk-usage alarm guards the Gerrit data volume.\n\n## Scope\nIn: containers, the external Gerrit data volume DECLARATION, base `gerrit.config`,\nnginx+TLS+certbot renewal, the review-bot receiver HTTP surface + hosting, SSM->.env secrets\nbootstrap, the SSM IAM instance role, minimal logging/health/disk observability. Out: Gerrit\nproject/label/submit-req (S3); the bot identity + event wiring + the receiver's review/vote\nLOGIC (S4 — S2 stands up the *service*, S4 wires its behavior); replication (S5); the data\nvolume's snapshot + retention policy (S7's DLM daily-snapshot policy owns it — S2 only declares\nthe volume).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`, `infra/compose/gerrit.config`, `infra/nginx/*.conf`\n  (incl. the `/.well-known/acme-challenge/` location and the `location /review/` upstream)\n- `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` (SSM -> ephemeral `.env`), bootstrap scripts under `infra/`\n  (install the certbot-renew timer, the health/disk checks)\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/` (the webhook-receiver ASGI service — skeleton/health endpoint in S2;\n  review+vote behavior in S4)\n- `docs/adr/0007-review-bot-receiver.md`, `docs/adr/0008-secrets-source-ssm.md`\n- `.gitignore` (ensure `infra/compose/.env` is ignored)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Gerrit is reachable at `https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/` with a valid Let's Encrypt cert.\n- [ ] A Gerrit change screen / a project path containing `%2F` renders correctly (encoded-slash round-trip verified end-to-end through nginx).\n- [ ] certbot renewal is automated: the timer/cron is installed + enabled, the nginx `/.well-known/acme-challenge/` location serves the HTTP-01 challenge, and `certbot renew --dry-run` succeeds and reloads nginx via the deploy-hook.\n- [ ] Gerrit SSH clone works on 29418 and the admin account is bootstrapped.\n- [ ] Gerrit data persists across `docker compose down/up` and an instance reboot; the data volume is `external: true` so `docker compose down -v` does not destroy it. (Snapshot + retention of this volume is owned by S7, not S2.)\n- [ ] The review-bot webhook receiver (a plain HTTP service importing the review kernel as a library, NOT the stdio MCP over HTTP) is reachable through nginx at `https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/review/` — a POST reaches the receiver process (not a 502); the decision is recorded in `docs/adr/0007-review-bot-receiver.md`.\n- [ ] The review-bot container's signing key + ANTHROPIC_API_KEY are sourced from SSM at boot by `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` into a `0600`, gitignored, ephemeral `.env` (never baked into the image/compose, never committed); the script authenticates via the instance role, is idempotent, and aborts if SSM is unreachable. The receiver's LLM review path is enabled by `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` + the `[agents]` extra alone (no `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` flag, which gates only the stdio MCP server, is set).\n- [ ] The SSM IAM instance role grants `GetParameter`/`GetParameters` scoped to `parameter/rebar/prod/*` only (no wildcard), verified against the attached policy.\n- [ ] Both containers log to `journald`; a health probe covers `/` and `/review/`, and a disk-usage alarm covers the Gerrit data volume.\n- [ ] Gerrit runs a supported version at an EXISTING arm64 patch tag (e.g. `gerritcodereview/gerrit:3.14.1`; a bare minor tag like `3.14` is NOT used — it doesn't exist), with `heapLimit=2g` and `packedGitLimit` budgeted within it.\n\n## Round-12 plan-review remediation (2026-06-30 — recalibrated gate BLOCK + critical advisories)\n\n**Blocking — internal sequencing (phased build, each phase verified before the next):**\n- **Phase 1 (riskiest first):** Gerrit `gerritcodereview/gerrit:3.14.1` (arm64) container up with the external data volume + base `gerrit.config`; reachable over plain HTTP through nginx (no TLS yet); `%2F`-encoded path round-trips. Proves the arm64 image + the `%2F`-safe proxy before anything else is layered on.\n- **Phase 2:** nginx TLS via certbot (Let's Encrypt) on 443 + the `/.well-known/acme-challenge/` webroot + the twice-daily `certbot renew` timer with the nginx-reload deploy-hook; `certbot renew --dry-run` green.\n- **Phase 3:** `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh` (SSM->ephemeral 0600 `.env`) via the instance role + the scoped IAM policy attachment (S2's separately-named inline policy on the S1-owned role).\n- **Phase 4:** the review-bot receiver container reachable through nginx at `/review/` (skeleton + health only — review/vote LOGIC is S4b).\n- **Phase 5:** observability (journald, `/` + `/review/` health probes, data-volume disk alarm).\n\n**Critical advisories folded in:**\n- **`webhooks` plugin is NOT bundled in the official image (seam to S4a):** S2 stands up the *service* only. The Gerrit site's `plugins/` dir is a bind-mount/volume path so a version-matched (3.14.1) `webhooks` + `events-log` plugin jar can be dropped in; ACTUAL plugin install + wiring is **S4a**. S2 verifies only that the site supports dropping plugin jars (the plugins dir is writable + on the persistent volume). No S2 AC depends on webhooks delivering events.\n- **Receiver framework dependency (was absent):** add a `reviewbot` optional extra to `pyproject.toml` = `fastapi` + `uvicorn[standard]`. The receiver container builds via `infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot` (`pip install .[agents,reviewbot]`). The stdio MCP server is untouched.\n- **Dockerfile added** to Files: `infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot`.\n- **`core.packedGitLimit` is OFF-HEAP (correction):** JGit's `core.packedGitLimit` is the mmap'd packfile budget, sized against TOTAL RAM, NOT inside the Java heap. Config: `container.heapLimit=2g` (on-heap) + `core.packedGitLimit` ~1g budgeted against the ~8 GB box RAM ALONGSIDE (not within) the heap, leaving headroom for the OS + the receiver container.\n- **`fetch-secrets.sh` explicit SSM-leaf -> env mapping** (the 7 params S1 created): `/rebar/prod/gerrit-admin-password`->`GERRIT_ADMIN_PASSWORD`, `gerrit-ssh-host-ed25519-key`->`GERRIT_SSH_HOST_ED25519_KEY`, `github-replication-deploy-key`->`GITHUB_REPLICATION_DEPLOY_KEY`, `mcp-hmac-signing-key`->`MCP_HMAC_SIGNING_KEY`, `anthropic-api-key`->`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `alert-endpoint`->`ALERT_ENDPOINT`, `gerrit-bot-token`->`GERRIT_BOT_TOKEN`. (Same contract as S1's user_data.sh; S2 sources only the subset the containers need.)\n- **LLM path enablement:** the receiver's LLM review path is enabled by `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` + the `[agents]` extra ALONE — `REBAR_MCP_ALLOW_LLM` (which gates only the stdio MCP server) is intentionally NOT set.\n- **External volume creation step:** the Gerrit data volume is a Docker `external: true` volume backed by the `/var/gerrit` EBS mount; `infra/scripts/compose-up.sh` (the boot orchestrator) runs `docker volume create --driver local --opt type=none --opt o=bind --opt device=/var/gerrit gerrit_data` (idempotent) BEFORE `docker compose up`, so a stray `docker compose down -v` cannot destroy it.\n- **Port single-source:** the receiver port is one env var `REVIEW_BOT_PORT` (default 8000) in the `.env`; compose and the nginx upstream both read it (nginx via an envsubst-templated conf at boot), so the two can't drift.\n\n**Added / updated ACs:**\n- [ ] The build is phased (Phase 1 Gerrit+HTTP -> 2 TLS -> 3 secrets/IAM -> 4 receiver -> 5 observability); Phase 1 reachability is proven before TLS is layered on.\n- [ ] `pyproject.toml` declares a `reviewbot` extra (fastapi + uvicorn); `infra/compose/Dockerfile.reviewbot` builds the receiver via `.[agents,reviewbot]`.\n- [ ] `gerrit.config` sets `container.heapLimit=2g` (on-heap) and `core.packedGitLimit` as a SEPARATE off-heap budget (~1g) sized against box RAM, NOT inside the heap.\n- [ ] `fetch-secrets.sh` maps the enumerated `/rebar/prod/*` leaves to the documented env-var names, writes a 0600 ephemeral `.env`, authenticates via the instance role, is idempotent, and aborts if SSM is unreachable.\n- [ ] The Gerrit data volume is created as an `external` bind volume on `/var/gerrit` by `compose-up.sh` before `docker compose up`; `docker compose down -v` does not destroy it.\n- [ ] The receiver port is single-sourced (`REVIEW_BOT_PORT`) and consumed by both compose and the nginx `/review/` upstream.\n- [ ] The Gerrit site `plugins/` dir is on the persistent volume + writable (so S4a can drop version-matched webhooks/events-log jars); no S2 AC depends on event delivery."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782781031884478001,"uuid":"3b4cc635-7e40-41a6-b6d9-e7d819f23df1"}